message.explanation: Unable to create filename. One or more items in the output name string can not be created.

message.text: Invalid syntax in output name string: %s
message.explanation: Output name string contains invalid literals. Check the format of the output name string.
Initialization function should be called only once.

message.text: Unable to form a date string. The resulting string is too large ( > %s characters) to be placed into a filename.
message.explanation: Date string can not be formatted. Refine date string to fit into filename length restrictions.
Unable to initialise counter for outputname creation. Check that literal syntax is correct.
Invalid sequence reset interval given. Check the given value.

message.text: Too many regular expression captures. Only 10 is allowed (found %s)
message.explanation: User has defined too many regular expression captures. Ten (10) is the maxmimum allowed amount. Refine your regular expression.

message.text: A regular expression capture did not capture anything. Index of the ineffective capture is: %s
message.explanation: A regular expresson capture did not capture anything. Check that the capture indexing starts from 1 and that the regular expressions are correct.

message.text: Too long sequence width. Maximum width is 19 digits, found %s digits.
message.explanation: Sequence can contain at maximum 19 digits. Refine sequence width to fit in the limits.

message.text: Invalid epoch 0 retrieved for %s. Using current time instead.
message.explanation: Invalid epoch value retrived from the internal storage. In order to avoid duplicate file names current time is used. Contact the vendor.

message.text: Undefined value given as a source id.
message.explanation: Source id has to be a non-null string. Correct the function call.
Unable to convert a string representation into a number representation.

message.text: Unable to read stored sequence value. Storage content possibly corrupted.
message.explanation: Correct the content of storage or remove it.
The status file is corrupted. Correct the contents or remove the status file.
Unable to write status file. Can not maintain integrity between executions. Check user write permissions.
Unable to allocate memory for output name string elements.
Node application using File Naming Library does not initiliaze CML.

message.text: Unable to form an output filename component %s string. The resulting string is too large ( > %s characters) to be placed into a filename.
message.explanation: One of the filename component strings can not be fit into defined space. Refine the OutputFileNameCreationMask parameter definition to have enough space for all components.
The regular expression syntax is incorrect. It can not be compiled.
The status info was unavailable or the contents were corrupted.
The parsing of output name string failed.

message.text: Regular expression didn't match any part of the filename.
message.explanation: The regular expression did not match any part of the filename. Verify that the regular expression is correct and designed for the filename used in this case.
Literal string was not recognized. Check that output name string syntax is correct.
